          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            @TacticalMastermind2.0- I didn't watch the game, just taking the mick out of Pulis and his rabbit-in-headlights tactics against top teams which usually results in sticking everybody behind the ball and hoping. I did see the highlights and the mini boost at 2-0 (instigated by the annoyed WBA fans). The 2 Aguero goals game from crap defending, albeit including a great finish, and you can't legislate for that. I agree his City team has struggled against aggressive pressers- Spurs in particular, but his Barcelona and Bayern teams tended to look far more comfortable when a team was attacking, because of the space it presents- which is paramount for his style, and uncomfortable when a team sat back and countered (Arsenal, Atletico Madrid, Celtic, Juventus, Real Madrid....). It's kind of the obvious game-plan against his teams. You need the players to be able to counter though and West Brom have none of those.
